title: 2 Bed Flat, Mount Pleasant Lane, E5
description: Upper Clapton: Light and airy 2-bedroom apartment in Victorian terrace conversion with plenty of outside spaceThe property is accessed from a quiet residential street via a large front garden with a communal seating area. A spacious hallway offers secure bicycle/pram storage for the 3 flats sharing this entrance. The split-level apartment is at raised ground floor at the front and offers a 15sqm roof terrace at the rear with views across the Walthamstow Marshes all the way to Canary Wharf. An external staircase connects down to a secluded private and mature garden at the back.Both double bedrooms have direct access to one of these outside spaces each, offer built-in storage solutions, tall ceilings and sea grass flooring. They share a brand new bathroom with a walk-in shower and the spacious open plan living area with a large bay, wooden floors, period features and a modern built-in kitchen with stone worktops, a gas hob and new integrated appliances.All rooms are bright and airy with either plantation shutters or purpose-made curtains. The windows are lockable timber sashes, draft-proofed with double glazing. Heating and hot water are via a gas combi-boiler with new radiators throughout.The property is being let fully furnished, including a dining area with a vintage church pew. The bed in the main bedroom ist 1.40m wide, in the upstairs bedroom the stacked futon single bed can be turned into a double. There are picture rail systems, so hanging your own artwork is possible.Clapton is a vibrant neighbourhood close to Dalston and Stoke Newington. The high street boasts the original Sodo pizzeria; down the road the Crooked Billet has a huge beer garden and the Clapton Hart at the round-about is best for Sunday roast (booking is essential!). There is the Tram Depot with its trendy gym, craft beer brewery and Tram Store Cafe. For the more authentic Hackney pub experience the Hope and Anchor on the river can't be beaten. In addition booze cruises now plough the Lea canal. Sparks Cafe in Springfield Park serves a consistently good breakfast and is about to return to its newly refurbished home in the White Villa. There is horse riding through the Marshes, a number of rowing clubs, tennis courts abound and a year-round ice rink minutes away (currently being rebuilt to be even better). The new Walthamstow Wetlands are around the corner and Westfield Shopping centre in Stratford can be reachedt via the Olympic Park in an easy 20min cycle ride.There are Co-op and Tesco supermarkets 5 minutes away, as well as excellent local stores; on Sundays there is also nearby Chatsworth Road market.It's a short walk to the nearby Clapton Overground station (Zone 2 and 3) which is 12min out of Liverpool Street on the Chingford line. It also connects north to Walthamstow Central and the Victoria Line in less than 5min. Also plenty of bus connections. The resident's parking scheme (Zone U) is about to be downgraded.Would suit couple or young family.Bills not included.Council tax band C.Cleaner included once a month.Please provide some background information re yourself with your enquiry.
